                        <p>
                            The integration of life skills in the curriculum and Social Outreach Initiatives has inculcated a system of values among the students. This has made them aware and sensitive towards the societal responsibility to the community and encouraged them to think
                            beyond the narrow confines of ‘I’ and reach out to connect compassionately with all.</p>
                            <p>
                                The role of school in child development begins as early as pre-school and continues through childhood. We not only provide a structured education but also promote a child’s mental and psychological growth. Aside from learning academics, the students are
                                provided experience to imbibe the life skills such as teamwork, good manners, unity, sharing, and responsibility in a safe environment.
                            </p>  
    
                    </div>
